      "role": "user",
      "content": "but u just said originalism is the \"most logically consistent\" framework. if it's more logical, then isn't the living constitution approach basically just making up rules to fit modern politics? it feels like one is based on actual law and the other is just whatever judges want it to be at the time. wouldn't you agree that one is actually legal science and the other is just activism?",
